::KitKat::
She smiled at War and DarkMouse. "It's nice to see you two getting 
long. Stay here.  Megatron said he was leaving. So I'm waiting for 
him to fall back and leave our terratory."

DarkMouse::
She looked up at KitKit and mutters,"Getting along is hardly the 
words I'd use."

KitKat::
She chuckled. "It's alright DarkMouse.  He probably saved your life 
out there."

DarkMouse:
"Like I'm worth saving."

KitKat::
She growled slightly,"Every bot on my teamis worth saving. You, 
Drillbit, Destructor, War, Famine, Starscream, they all are worth 
saving and fighting for.  You are no different than anyone else in my 
pack. You are just as important to my team as all the others.  
Everyone is worth it. Every single bot on my team is worth fighting 
for. And don't you forget it."

DarkMouse:
She walked off into the ship, mumbling about how she wasn't like the 
others.

KitKat::
She shook her head and looked up at War,"She's been like that since 
she was with Megatron. I feel sorry for her. She was programmed by a 
bot named Scorponok. Ever since, she's been in this, deep blue funk 
so to speak. One day, she'll come around. I'm certain of it. All it 
will take is a little time."
She looked out across the field and then back at War, "Would you 
please go to the bridge and check the long range scanners.  I want to 
make sure that Megatron is leaving the area."
